<br>
The man was Gunnaer Warhammer, a Shaman from the Northlands and merchant. He had basically retired from the Shamanic trade years ago, and spent his days selling off rare treasures he came across when exploring in abandoned ruins and mountains. When trade and travel across the Commonlands ceased three weeks ago, he was devastated: it was the best place to sell his wares. <br>
<br>
A few nights ago, the monsters had simply disappeared.<br>
<br>
He had been discussing this turn of events with a very odd Dark Elf the night before. The Elf seemed interested in any reports of monsters that could be found, whether they were in the Commonlands, or half a world away. He had kept muttering something about those &quot;God damned fools in the court.&quot; When Gunnaer asked what he meant, the other had only replied &quot;Nothing, nothing...&quot; The man had set Gunnaer's mind going, and he was ready to head north to Nektulos to check out the scene there. As a trader, he was on friendly terms with most races, save the Iksar, Heretics of Paineel, and Trolls. The Tier'dal tolerated his presence as long as he brought interesting wares. He had something that he was sure would perk their interest.<br>
<br>
~~~<br>
<br>
Iommi snapped awake to see the shape standing in front of him. &quot;Magus?!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Silent Iommi. Remember, you may be banned from ever coming to Trium again, but you are my eyes and ears here. The Dragons are unusually active, I need you to find out what the hell is going on. Trium is still being torn apart by a thousand tiny wars, yet no one sees the large one on the horizon. You need to keep track of what goes on here, so I don't have to worry about it.&quot;<br>
<br>
Iommi sighed and nodded. &quot;Magus...&quot;<br>
<br>
The elder mage didn't let him speak anymore. The tall man turned, walked away, and faded into nothing. <p><center><BR>
