<br>
Gehennabringer was a mysterious man, always had been, and prided himself in that fact. There were rumors he was a direct descendant of Mistmoore, or of Dragons, or even someone from a different <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> planet</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. Perhaps none of them were true, perhaps all of them. It didn't matter: he was a traitor to the Dead and the Crown, and Queen Christanos Thex wanted him dead.<br>
<br>
&quot;I hear...that Gehennabringer eluded your best men a few months ago, that he escaped from the under-city prisons. You ought to be ashamed. Letting this man escape from right under your noses <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> twice</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.&quot;<br>
<br>
The ancient, shrouded, skeletal figure of the Queen of the Dead wished to speak. In the rare instances she spoke, she made it known telepathically. She was in failing health, reportedly from experimenting on herself, and almost constantly being in the form of a lich or some other undead creature. Rumors were that she supported herself by taking living sacrifices. Rumors were probably true, in this case. She barely had the strength to speak, much less raise her hand or move forward. Her voice was thin and raspy. She was constantly under a black veil, barely visible, but her bone-thin limbs and body were all too apparent. No one dared think of her dying for good and letting someone ascend the throne, the last person who had, was never seen again after that meeting.<br>
<br>
The Queen of the Dead had also ascended to the throne herself after Iommi's mother had been assassinated. She was Lynaela Gehennabringer's successor...and predecessor. She was the first Queen of the Dead. Others had come and gone, but she had led in between each one. She vowed Lynaela would be the last woman to be Queen of the Dead besides her, until she died.<br>
<br>
&quot;Gehennabringer comes from a long line of powerful beings,&quot; the voice hissed. &quot;His foster father was the leader of the Warpriests. How did he die? Iommi poisoned the food his mother sent with him when he went off on the great war with the Knights of Truth. His foster mother was one of mine. How did she die? Stabbed in the back by her own adopted son. And if he truly is descended from that bastard Mistmoore...he is one to be feared. Who knows what spies he could have among us? He was our most adept, our darkest, our most powerful. He could have undead all over the city, watching, waiting. The way to end the matter is simple...we find him...and we destroy him. Forever.&quot; <p><center>
